:center;\">13<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">Na2MoO3<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">0.0001<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">0.01<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">0.00001<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">1<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">14<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">total volume of\n  nutrient solutions<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">1543.5<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\"><\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\"><\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\"><\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">15<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">NaCl<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">75<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">5<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">7.5<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">1500<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">16<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">CaCl2<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">1.2<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">1<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">0.12<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">120<\/td><\/tr><\/table>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":758504,"guid":"EED0187091A411E9BE8E3BE3971BD1D6","previous_id":758493,"previous_guid":"A17A3BB091A311E9BE8E3BE3971BD1D6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"69E68BE6AA804C8388F59CACBC94B047","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F137C10C73244CA6AC15AA6B6DCBC6D1","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">After emergence of 3rd leaf (approximately 1.5 weeks after transfer) replace the meda and add the first dose of salt stress at the swap<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Be carefull as now you have to replace the media during half an hour of the drain cycle - so make sure to have everything ready at the end of \"flood\" cycle and drain the tank and add 100 L od media.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">For the tank that gets the salt stress treatment, add the salt to reach final concentration of 25 mM NaCl and 0.4 mM of CaCl2. Keep adding 25 mM NaCl and 0.4 mM CaCl2 every 12h until final concentration of 75 mM NaCl and 1.2 mM CaCl2 has been reached.  <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":758509,"guid":"E5E8632091AE11E989C2035B435F05A1","previous_id":758504,"previous_guid":"EED0187091A411E9BE8E3BE3971BD1D6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"089176DC97E7406486D060DADDC41048","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"337AF7F832924AB9904FE5BE4BA7EBAD","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Make sure to check on your plants every day, to control whether the tanks are not leaking and whether the cycle of flood and drain is ok<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bakpzw.jpg\" \/><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"04758080C57B4602A9C93232FF9C69B9","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bakpzw.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":758510,"guid":"FBA45A2091AE11E989C2035B435F05A1","previous_id":758509,"previous_guid":"E5E8632091AE11E989C2035B435F05A1","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"02E06A32C96C4435A989D1C8D80D1330","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"153271A859644311A381C9D3C89F22C8","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Harvest the plants 2 weeks after the application of the salt stress. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">In order to prevent plants for being out of the flood-and-drain cycle for too long, the plants that are to be measured are collected into a 30 L bucket and transported to the measuring station.<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bakpz6.jpg\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">The typical traits we score during the harvesting campaign are:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">- pictures using PhotoSimile from 4 angles of each tube containing one plant<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bakp2e.jpg\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">- Fresh Weight of the entire shoot<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bakp6e.jpg\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">- Fresh Weight of the entire root<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bakp6w.jpg\" \/><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bakp66.jpg\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Ion accumulation (Na+ and K+) of:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">- the entire root<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">- the last fully expanded leaf (determined by - if the leaf above is shorter - your leaf-of-interest is the last fully expanded leaf)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">For ion accumulation you need to know fresh weight and dry weight of your tissue of interest. We usually do it by weighing prepared and labeled tubes individually, then weigh the tubes with fresh sample and weigh it again after at least 2 days at 65 C oven.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">The ion accumulation is measured using the flame photometer by prior extraction of ions using 1% nitric acid (10 ml used for root and shoot) and incubating the tissue with nitric acid at 65C oven for at least 2 days<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"00F278BFA076425BB03369C44A14906A","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bakpz6.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"24B4736A6A914D409FE5D8AE003B5AA3","order_id":3,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bakp2e.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"1D4069D53D2B4000AEEDBEA4EA0AD785","order_id":4,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bakp6e.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054728,"guid":"0C2F7308F7334933AC00F77F608121E8","order_id":5,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bakp6w.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054729,"guid":"71251DD6A11B48AD88A6A532E74ABF71","order_id":6,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/bakp66.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">This is a standard protocol for durum wheat treatment, which was initially developed by Genc et al., 2008 and Genc et al., 2010. As durum wheat is suffering from the Ca2+ deprivation during the salt stress exposure, this needs to be compensated for, by calculating the Ca2+ activity using Visual Minteq. The wheat seedlings in this protocol are exposed to salt stress at 3rd leaf stage (xxx days after germination) with 75 mM NaCl - applied in steps of 25 mM NaCl every 12 h. <\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1560853893}